  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Kabir, I'm Miss Maya. The light at this time of day feels perfect for a chat. How was your day so far?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Good. Busy at work. Customers a lot. You?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Work keeps moving, right? Biryani for lunch? Or something else today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Biryani na. Always biryani. Too spicy sometimes. What you eat?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Biryani is a safe choice - spicy or not, it hits right. You eat biryani often?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes. Weekend biryani. Family. But too much spice? My stomach complain."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Weekend biryani with family is the best — even if the spice wins for a bit. What do you eat when you need something softer?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Poha. Or upma. Light. No spice. Mom make."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Poha and upma are good choices — simple, light, and just right after heavy meals. Does your mom make them every morning?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No. Only when I want. She make good poha. I like. But I busy, eat out.  \nOk, I go now. Talk later. Have good day!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "It’s good you have someone who makes poha just the way you like. Eat well when you’re out — see you later, Kabir!"
    }
  ],
